This paper deals with learning predictive models for robots from both interaction and observation data. The paper discusses the challenges of learning complex skills and the need for augmenting the training set with observational data of other agents, such as humans. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Robotics (cs.RO), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of videos, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a domain-dependent prior, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
